  "local_port": 32844,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good NGOs working in the field of children's education in India?",
  "response": "There are several excellent NGOs in India dedicated to improving children's education. Here are some notable ones:\n\n1. **Pratham**  \n   - **Focus**: Pratham is one of the largest NGOs in India, working to improve the quality of education for underprivileged children. They focus on literacy and numeracy through innovative teaching methods and community involvement.\n   - **Website**: [pratham.org](https://www.pratham.org)\n\n2. **Teach For India**  \n   - **Focus**: This organization recruits and trains young professionals to teach in under-resourced schools, aiming to bridge the educational gap. They also work on leadership development in the education sector.\n   - **Website**: [teachforindia.org](https://www.teachforindia.org)\n\n3. **Akshaya Patra Foundation**  \n   - **Focus**: While primarily known for its mid-day meal program, Akshaya Patra also supports educational initiatives by ensuring children stay in school through better nutrition.\n   - **Website**: [akshayapatra.org](https://www.akshayapatra.org)\n\n4. **Room to Read**  \n   - **Focus**: Room to Read focuses on literacy and gender equality in education. They work on establishing libraries, publishing books in local languages, and supporting girls' education.\n   - **Website**: [roomtoread.org](https://www.roomtoread.org)\n\n5. **Smile Foundation**  \n   - **Focus**: Smile Foundation runs various programs, including \"Mission Education,\" which aims to provide quality education to underprivileged children across India.\n   - **Website**: [smilefoundationindia.org](https://www.smilefoundationindia.org)\n\n6. **CRY (Child Rights and You)**  \n   - **Focus**: CRY works on ensuring children's rights, including access to education. They partner with grassroots organizations to address systemic issues affecting children's education.\n   - **Website**: [cry.org](https://www.cry.org)\n\n7. **Kat-Katha**  \n   - **Focus**: Kat-Katha works with children in red-light areas, providing them with education and life skills to break the cycle of poverty and exploitation.\n   - **Website**: [kat-katha.org](https://www.kat-katha.org)\n\n8. **Make A Difference (MAD)**  \n   - **Focus**: MAD works with children in orphanages and shelters to provide educational support, mentorship, and resources to help them succeed academically.\n   - **Website**: [makeadiff.in](https://www.makeadiff.in)\n\n9. **Salaam Baalak Trust**  \n   - **Focus**: This organization works with street and working children in urban areas, providing education, shelter, and healthcare to help them reintegrate into mainstream society.\n   - **Website**: [salaambaalaktrust.com](https://www.salaambaalaktrust.com)\n\n10. **Educate Girls**  \n    - **Focus**: Educate Girls focuses on enrolling out-of-school girls in rural India and improving the quality of education through community mobilization and curriculum development.\n    - **Website**: [educategirls.ngo](https://www.educategirls.ngo)\n\nThese NGOs are making significant contributions to children's education in India, often working in collaboration with government bodies, local communities, and other stakeholders to create lasting impact. Supporting or volunteering with any of these organizations can make a meaningful difference in the lives of underprivileged children.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
